Keware is a village and gram panchayat in India, situated in Mawal taluka of Pune district in the state of Maharashtra. It encompasses an area of .
Administration
The village is administrated by a sarpanch, an elected representative who leads a gram panchayat. At the time of the 2011 Census of India, the village was the headquarters for the eponymous gram panchayat, which also governed the village of Chavsar.
Demographics
At the 2011 census, the village comprised 7 households. The population of 47 was split between 23 males and 24 females.
Air travel connectivity
The closest airport to the village is Pune Airport.
